reviews.text: Great park. Nice disc golf course throughout. Geese poop everywhere so try not to feed them. Has a family of Peacocks near duck pond and is a good place for open houses, receptions, and family reunions.

I love Lake Shore park! It may not be the biggest or most scenic lake Erie beach but it's good enough and I found this to be the best park to go to with small kids. The gated playground is right on the beach, the restrooms are conveniently located, there are concessions, and there is a pond with ducks, geese, swans, and even a peacock house. There's a classic car show every Sunday and their rib burn off is held every September; free family fun, even for those of us who don't like ribs.
It's a beautiful clean park. The lake is so big. The landscaping well done and in great positions. The ducks, swans, and geese are all so friendly. No dogs but that was fine for this park.
Very nice park. During Christmas they put on a wonderful light display. Kept clean and in good repair.
Only good park in ashtabula great place for reunions picnics and gatherings.. great light show for the holidays
Amazing tour. Great to know the history of the area. Mrs. Hubbard was there to greet us and made us feel welcomed
What a wonderful staff of volunteers. Great piece of Ashtabula history
We enjoyed the Very knowledgeable tour guide. They have great displays, and history seem to come alive.
Very informative,reasonably priced has interesting artifacts a gem in ashtabula

The amazing house provided food, shelter and clothing for slaves escaping the South. The house was once called Mother Hubbard’s Cupboard and The Great Emporium, it is listed on the US Department of the Interior National Register of Historic Places.

I love the food here! No matter what I order I am always incredibly pleased!! My favorite dish is the lamb chops dish! The atmosphere is cozy and intimate with extremely helpful and fun staff! Alessandro is a wizard in the kitchen! 10/10 would recommend.
Just an amazing meal. We had a  group of six so we had to wait for awhile as they don't take reservations.  Definitely worth the wait  Fun wait staff.
We love Alessandro's! Great food right on the lake. Lovely little place!!

We have passed this place many times and finally decided to go last night. All I can say is we will NEVER go back! Been to many Italian restaurants and have always left stuffed and with a to go container. I was utterly shocked when the food came out! The dinner portions were smaller than an appetizer, the salad was nothing more than a few pieces of lettuce with horrible italian dressing and a tomato wedge. $1.50 for a handful of mozzarella cheese on top! Bread was cold, as was the butter served with it. Water tasted like mildew. Food was OK but not worth almost TWENTY dollars a plate!!! My mom ordered eggplant parmigiana, 2 small pieces, no pasta, just the eggplant! Our waitress was very nice, but not worth almost $100 for 4 people and we left hungry!! If you aren't hungry and dont mind paying a small fortune, this is your place.

When you find a good place you just have to go back. Very good Italian cooking here, large parking lot, bathroom better than mine at home (excellent tile), wine is available with dinner, see the cook in action behind the counter, good service. Now I'm getting hungry again. A good stop for dinner after 4pm.

The food is amazing, but the portions are kinda small for the cost. But what do you expect at the only true 5 star restaurant in the entire county! I dont eat there often, but the food, drinks, staff etc are first class all around! I highly recommend this fine restaurant to take a date to if you wanna have a great time with great food and drinks, and an impeccable atmosphere and staff line up!

As an employee of Casa Capelli, i have been for 8 years. This place has the most familial comfortable atmosphere. The ones who complain about this place had a bad experience.  It doesn't make it every experience every time. Yes we run out of items because our food is fresh, instead of places that have their food shipped in already packaged and frozen. Everything is homemade!  If anyone listens to these reviews, take my advice...don't. its an experience you won't want to miss!
Very clean and comfortable atmosphere but rather pricey........
4 stars for atmosphere and delicious food.

We came here with some friends were visiting and we loved it. We all shared different dishes and they were all delicious. Try the Italian dishes and finger food. You won’t be disappointed. The Beer Battered Cod was just right. Nice people, good food, and good prices.
It was amazing. The staff was nice and we'll organized. I would really recommend it for a lunch date with family friends or just a significant other. ❤️❤️❤️🤞🤞🤞
Been going here since I was little. Great food esp when Dan cooks it, great prices, awesome waitresses, & a friendly environment! Would definitely recommend this place! 💯💯
Dan makes an excellent 🎖️Grilled Chicken salad 🥗 and Taco 🌮 Salad. Sue gave us fast and friendly service. Deserts are awesome also.
the service is great the food is even greater anyone that enjoys good food you need to try this restaurant yummy yummy yummy yummy for the tummy tummy tummy that's all I can say

The Staff was professional , polite and courteous even during a very busy Saturday evening.

The chicken parmigiana was well presented surrounded by the various pastas- spaghetti, ravioli, and rigatoni ; although more sauce was required and it’s flavor needed more of a boost with garlic , herbs , beef stock and longer cooking .

I respect a family owned and operated business and the menu detailed the origin of the restaurant and the Son who attended CIA and returned home to develop the restaurant business further .  

I’m happy to have this fine establishment in my neighborhood and will return again .
Love the fresh baked goods and friendly service here. Great 0lace for breakfast.
Good for lunch or dinner but specially if you like seafood prices aren't over the top for no ocean in sight although there is the lake! Good service as well.
We always enjoying eating at Lakeway. Very good food and friendly staff.
Better place to eat in Ashtabula. Good food. Friendly staff

Don't order from here as if you fall asleep you don't get your order or your money back so please don't order from little Italy pizza really bad review go to pizza hut as its a lot better than this place

I moved out of Aberdeen a year ago and what a loss it is not to have Little Italy around.. I simply cannot find a pizza restaurant with the same quality pizzas as this.

Expand! And for every newcomers, I highly recommend the Little Italy Calzone 12" if you like a bit spicy food!
Their sizes are a bit on the small side but otherwise great value for your money.

I went and ordered food throigh their website. The order was rejected due to them being too busy which I totally understand. However they proceeded to charge me twice and took the money out of my account. I emailed them and have not received any response. I am really not happy with this and this is slmesomet that people need to be avare off

The pizza is very good. I would say 7/10. I have tried the piri piri one and calzone. The number of ingredients in calzone is perfect. No option to order garlic sauce. Only garlic mayo available which taste very average. It is so easy to make garlic sauce, it should be a problem for the pizza place. The delivery time was shocking, 1:35, during the week. I cannot imagine waiting time during the peak times. Furthermore, the place is quite dear. It is not real Italian pizza therefore price should be lower. Why do I need to pay extra fee while ordering online through your website. I see the potential but some changes must be done.
Love this place!! We have never had a bad experience. Food is always great and service is always great.

The decor is fun with lots of cool knick knacks to look at. The people who work there are friendly. The salsa was awesome. The cheese enchilada was very good. The restaurant is clean and the people work hard. The taco was bland and lacking seasoning. The chips, while tasty, seemed stale and lacked that snap and crunch I expected. The cheese dip was bland and lacked spices. The night we were there, they were quite busy and service was slow and subpar. Drinks, chip refills and special requests such as sour cream came out very slowly.

I gave them a 3 because I think my visit this time was average, not exceptional nor terrible. I would eat there again. Many of the issues I mention above are correctable; it is entirely possible that on another visit I would have better service and more seasoned food and would then give this restaurant a much higher rating.
Awesome food and service. Great clean atmosphere. Great staff and the manager was very hospitable and friendly.
Amazing food at great prices! What more can you ask for?!?  The staff is always courteous. The portions are good sized and fill you up. 😊

Best Mexican restaurant in town! The food is always fantastic. The atmosphere is great. The staff and ownership treat you like family. Rarely is there an issue with your order and the service is fast! It’s great for a quick work lunch! Try the cheese dip!
Food is excellent, made fresh with excellent service. Does take a while bur well worth the wait. If it's cold outside bring a warm jacket.
Its a hidden gem. Food is fantastic. Their lunch menu is so inexpensive but you get plenty of food. I recommend this restaurant highly.
Great food ...but....long wait ....it worth it.....i think
Bourbon chicken was awesome fried rice taste burnt

The best chinese cuisine around! Prepared to order and fresh so it takes some time so be prepared on being there approx 1.5 hours. As we wait we play games and enjoy each other's company while sipping tea. The food is way under priced. Family owned and operated the best around, so worth the wait, I won't go anywhere else!

Amazing dinner last night 5 floors above our room! The view is gorgeous 😍😍 The staff is amazing and friendly. Boy oh boy it was the BEST food I have EVER had at a restaurant. The pork chop literally melted in my mouth and the brussel sprout leaves that came with was to die for! Highly highly recommend this place for special occasions!!!

Very fancy food. You definitely get what you pay for. I would recommend going when the sun is up or you will end up looking into the dark void that is Alaskan nights. Servers are on top of their game.

The service was wonderful, Ryan. The wine was very good. Love the setting and the scenery. The salmon was a too fresh. It was raw in the middle. Disappointed in the salmon. The squash soup was good. Very expensive.
Unbelievable experience, unlike any other! Incredible views and food. Pocketbook will be lighter after going here (we had four people in our group) but one of the best meals possible in Alaska!!!

I visit every month with my friends from the now defunct Rotary Club of Tring. My personal experience is therefore only relevant to Wednesday lunch times. The service on Wednesdays is very good, with two very friendly and helpful waitresses. The food is good value and would never claim to be Cordon Bleu. It is a good example of a pub serving traditional British food. Inexpensive and simple.
